The client initially provides a @a switch_editor/@a switch_baton to the RA layer; this editor contains knowledge of where the change will begin in the working copy (when open_root() is called).
In return, the client receives a @a reporter/@a report_baton. The client then describes its working copy by making calls into the @a reporter.
When finished, the client calls @a reporter->finish_report(). The RA layer then does a complete drive of @a switch_editor, ending with close_edit(), to switch the working copy.
@a switch_target is an optional single path component will restrict the scope of things affected by the switch to an entry in the directory represented by the @a session's URL, or empty if the entire directory is meant to be switched.
